<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-777-570  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 777 570.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  August 6 1990 v219 n6 p9(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Devil's Island becomes heavens' door. (telecommunicationssatellite-launching business in French Guiana) (News of the Week)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Luxner, Larry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Devil's Island, once a prison colony, is now in the forefront ofthe global telecommunications satellite-launching business.andP;  Morethan half the non-Communist world's satellites are launched fromthe European Space Agency's (ESA's) Kourou Space Center, which islocated in French Guiana, a department of France in northeasternSouth America.andP;  Kourou's location - only 5 degrees north of theequator, where the earth's rotation is fastest - allows satellitesto achieve a geostationary transfer orbit (GTO) with 17 percentless fuel than is needed if a satellite is launched from CapeCanaveral.andP;  Kourou now accounts for 90 percent of French Guiana'sprosperity.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     French GuianaCommunications Satellites.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>